cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NE, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with maintaining shortest path distances in a dynamic digraph undergoing edge deletions, which is a classic problem in data structures and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are both likely categories. The paper also involves analyzing the performance of different data structures against an adaptive or oblivious adversary, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.NE (Computer Science and Networking). Finally, the paper presents improved update times compared to previous work, which is relevant to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
